function initials(name: string) {
  const parts = name.split('&').map((p) => p.trim()).filter(Boolean);
  if (parts.length > 1) {
    return parts.map((p) => p.split(/\s+/)[0][0]).join('').toUpperCase();
  }
  const words = parts[0].split(/\s+/);
  return (words[0][0] + (words[1]?.[0] ?? '')).toUpperCase();
}
---

<BaseLayout title="About TVC" description="Why Tamarind Valley Collective exists, what we stand for, and the people — founding members, other members, and local staff — behind it." image="/images/pages/home/gallery-1.jpg" imageWidth={768} imageHeight={576}>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="About TVC"
    title="Why TVC?"
    intro="A collective of 53 families regenerating a 100-acre farm through permaculture, and the community — on and off the farm — that makes it possible."
    image="/images/pages/home/gallery-1.jpg"
    imageAlt="Aerial view of TVC's thatched huts on the hillside"
  />

  <section class="section wrapper">
    <h2>What we stand for</h2>

    <h3>Vision</h3>
    <p>To be a model regenerative farm community — stewarding land as one ecosystem, sharing knowledge freely, and proving that a small, disciplined community can create outsized positive impact.</p>

    <h3>Mission</h3>
    <p>We unite individuals committed to sustainable living to build a low-energy, permaculture farm that connects rather than competes with nature, ensuring a fair share for birds and beasts alongside our own. Through shared labor, native seed banking, and disciplined land stewardship, we aim to demonstrate that regenerative farming can uplift both ecosystems and neighboring communities.</p>

    <p>As the name indicates, TVC is a collective of like-minded people who have come together to evolve a sustainable living concept. We are currently <a href="#members">53 families</a> that care about the degradation of natural resources globally and would like to experiment with a living style that reduces consumption and incorporates naturally supported cyclical systems.</p>
    <p>TVC is a 100-acre farm collectively owned by these families. Due to exploitative farming practices, the farmland was degraded when we bought it. Since 2017, the community has been using permaculture principles to regenerate the farm's fertility naturally.</p>

    <h3>Farming, the TVC way</h3>
    <p>One of the core principles of the community is to practice sustainable farming — meeting current food needs without harming the environment or compromising future generations' ability to meet theirs, using methods like crop rotation, integrated pest management, water conservation, and reducing chemical inputs to create resilient food systems.</p>

    <div class="two-col">
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Core principles &amp; goals</h4>
        <ul>
          {PRINCIPLES.map((p) => (
            <li><strong>{p.name}:</strong> {p.desc}</li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h4>Common practices</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Crop rotation</strong> to replenish soil nutrients.</li>
          <li><strong>Integrated pest management</strong> using natural predators.</li>
          <li><strong>Cover crops</strong> to prevent erosion and improve soil.</li>
          <li><strong>Water conservation</strong> via drip irrigation and rainwater harvesting.</li>
          <li><strong>Composting &amp; mulching</strong> to build soil organic matter.</li>
          <li><strong>Agroecology</strong> — designing the farm to mimic natural ecosystems.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>Industrial agriculture often prioritizes high yields through monocultures and heavy chemical use. Sustainable farming aims for a holistic system instead — producing healthy food while regenerating natural resources and supporting local economies.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--tint" id="members">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <h2>Member families</h2>
      <p>The 53 families who make up the collective — most joined between the founding in 2017 and today.</p>
      <div class="members-grid">
        {members.map((m) => (
          <div class="member-card">
            {m.photo ? (
              <img src={m.photo} alt={m.name} class="member-photo" loading="lazy" />
            ) : (
              <div class="member-photo member-photo--placeholder" aria-hidden="true">{initials(m.name)}</div>
            )}
            <h4>{m.name}</h4>
            {m.bio && <p>{m.bio}</p>}
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section wrapper">
    <h2>Our local staff and community</h2>
    <p>The day-to-day activities at the farm are managed by a small, dedicated team living on-site.</p>
    <div class="staff-grid">
      {staff.map((s) => (
        <div class="card">
          <h4>{s.name}</h4>
          <p class="staff-role">{s.role}</p>
          <p>{s.bio}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section wrapper">
    <h2>Partners &amp; collaborators</h2>
    <p>Beyond the farm's own community, a handful of organizations have supported TVC along the way — from hospitality to permaculture design.</p>
    <a class="button button--outline" href="/ecosystem/partners">Meet our partners →</a>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--tint" id="join">
    <div class="wrapper join">
      <h2>Interested in becoming a member?</h2>
      <p>Membership isn't really open — 53 families is close to as large as this community will get. When a spot does open, it passes privately between members rather than through any application process. Here's exactly how that works.</p>
      <a class="button" href="/join">Read how it works →</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .two-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: 20px;
    margin: 24px 0;
  }

  .members-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(150px, 1fr));
    gap: 18px;
    margin-top: 20px;
  }

  .member-card {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--tvc-line);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
    padding: 16px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .member-card h4 {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .member-card p {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--tvc-ink-soft);
    margin: 6px 0 0;
  }

  .member-photo {
    width: 64px;
    height: 64px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    object-fit: cover;
    margin: 0 auto 10px;
    display: block;
  }

  .member-photo--placeholder {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: var(--tvc-green-tint);
    color: var(--tvc-green-dark);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .staff-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 20px;
    margin-top: 20px;
  }

  .staff-role {
    color: var(--tvc-orange);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .join {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
</style>
